<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  CANON REVIEW — monthly "reviewer of the reviewers" — installed 2026-06-20.

  Closes the second half of the ADAPTS loop. The nightly adaptation-proposer is
  REACTIVE and per-output (it retunes the agent that produced a weak output). This
  runs the `canon-review` Claude routine, which dispatches the PROACTIVE, doc-level
  `canon-reviewer` agent: it audits the CANON itself — the content-standard docs
  (Discoverability_Playbook, Master_Character_Prompt, On_Model_Verification_Protocol)
  and the reviewer rubrics (script-reviewer, image-reviewer) — for staleness/drift
  against (a) fresh youtube-researcher intel about what the platform rewards NOW and
  (b) the accumulated adaptation OUTCOME scoreboard (which past edits actually moved
  the needle). For each standing canon line the evidence shows has gone stale, it
  DRAFTS a surgical cited edit into the SAME /adapt queue Steve already approves, in
  the SAME format — so the deterministic apply core (scripts/adaptation.py), the
  /adapt approval flow, and the outcome-tagging loop all apply unchanged. The agent
  NEVER applies; Steve one-taps `/adapt approve <id>`.

  Runs via run_claude_job.sh (NOT run_job.sh): it's a `claude --print` routine, so
  the SAME wrapper every other claude-code job uses handles logging, the
  ROUTINE_COMPLETE/INCOMPLETE sentinel → Telegram alert, and the retry queue.

  Schedule: MONTHLY on the 1st at 5:30 AM ET. Canon doesn't go stale nightly and
  the audit needs accumulated outcome data + a month of fresh intel to judge drift,
  so a monthly cadence (matching contradiction-detector / credential-check) is the
  right altitude. canon-reviewer is evidence-gated + idempotent: a month with no
  stale canon line drafts ZERO proposals and reports a clean no-op — it never spams.
  5:30 on the 1st is a free slot after pre-brief (5:00 daily) and clear of the other
  1st-of-month jobs (credential-check 4:15, contradiction-detector 4:45). Bump to a
  fortnightly cadence later if the loop accumulates enough outcome signal to warrant.

  Manage:
    launchctl bootout gui/$(id -u)/com.iris.claude-code-canon-review 2>/dev/null
    cp scripts/com.iris.claude-code-canon-review.plist ~/Library/LaunchAgents/
    launchctl bootstrap gui/$(id -u) ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.iris.claude-code-canon-review.plist
    launchctl kickstart -k gui/$(id -u)/com.iris.claude-code-canon-review   # test fire
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<key>Label</key>
	<string>com.iris.claude-code-canon-review</string>
	<key>ProgramArguments</key>
	<array>
		<string>/bin/bash</string>
		<string>-lc</string>
		<string>/Volumes/AI_Workspace/iris_studio/scripts/run_claude_job.sh canon-review /Volumes/AI_Workspace/iris_studio/routines/canon-review.prompt</string>
	</array>
	<key>RunAtLoad</key>
	<false/>
	<key>StandardErrorPath</key>
	<string>/Users/steve/iris_studio/logs/canon-review.stderr.log</string>
	<key>StandardOutPath</key>
	<string>/Users/steve/iris_studio/logs/canon-review.stdout.log</string>
	<key>StartCalendarInterval</key>
	<dict>
		<key>Day</key>
		<integer>1</integer>
		<key>Hour</key>
		<integer>5</integer>
		<key>Minute</key>
		<integer>30</integer>
	</dict>
</dict>
</plist>
